#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:165
msgid ""
"The partition created by the **standard partition** cannot dynamically "
"adjust the resources of the hard disk, once the partition is mounted, the "
"capacity is completely fixed, this constraint is unacceptable on the server. "
"Although the standard partition can be forcibly expanded or shrunk through "
"certain technical means, it is easy to cause data loss. LVM can solve this "
"problem very well. LVM is available under Linux from kernel version 2.4, and "
"its main features are:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:171
msgid "More flexible disk capacity;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:171
msgid "Online data movement;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:171
msgid "Disks in _stripe_ mode;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:171
msgid "Mirrored volumes (recopy);"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:171
msgid "Volume snapshots (_snapshot_)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:173
msgid "The principle of LVM is very simple:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:177
msgid ""
"a logical abstraction layer is added between the physical disk (or disk "
"partition) and the file system"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:177
msgid "merge multiple disks (or disk partition) into Volume Group(**VG**)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:177
msgid ""
"perform underlying disk management operations on them through something "
"called Logical Volume(**LV**)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:179
#, no-wrap
msgid "**The physical media**: The storage medium of the LVM can be the entire hard disk, disk partition, or RAID array. The device must be converted, or initialized, to an LVM Physical Volume(**PV**), before further operations can be performed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:181
#, no-wrap
msgid "**PV(Physical Volume)**: The basic storage logic block of LVM. To create a physical volume, you can use a disk partition or the disk itself.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:183
#, no-wrap
msgid "**VG(Volume Group)**: Similar to physical disks in a standard partition, a VG consists of one or more PV.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:185
#, no-wrap
msgid "**LV(Logical Volume)**: Similar to hard disk partitions in standard partitions, LV is built on top of VG. You can set up a file system on LV.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:187
#, no-wrap
msgid "<b><font color=\"blue\">PE</font></b>: The smallest unit of storage that can be allocated in a Physical Volume, default to <b>4MB</b>. You can specify an additional size.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:189
#, no-wrap
msgid "<b><font color=\"blue\">LE</font></b>: The smallest unit of storage that can be allocated in a Logical Volume. In the same VG, PE and LE are the same and correspond one to one.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:191
msgid "![Volume group, PE size equal to 4MB](images/07-file-systems-004.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:193
msgid ""
"The disadvantage is that if one of the physical volumes becomes out of "
"order, then all the logical volumes that use this physical volume are lost. "
"You will have to use LVM on raid disks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:195
msgid "!!! note"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:197
#, no-wrap
msgid "    LVM is only managed by the operating system. Therefore the _BIOS_ needs at least one partition without LVM to boot.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:199
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:299
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:597
