#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:889
msgid ""
"Only the administrator and the owner of a file can change the rights of a "
"file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:890
#, no-wrap
msgid "`chmod` command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:893
msgid ""
"The `chmod` command allows you to change the access permissions to a file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:894
#, no-wrap
msgid "chmod [option] mode file\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:901
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Option |\tObservation                                                           |\n"
"|--------|------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n"
"| `-R`   |  Recursively change the permissions of the directory and all files under the directory. |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/admin_guide/07-file-systems.md:905
#, no-wrap
msgid "    The rights of files and directories are not dissociated. For some operations, it will be necessary to know the rights of the directory containing the file. A write-protected file can be deleted by another user as long as the rights of the directory containing it allow this user to perform this operation.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
